OL,4,CEx-BBC boss Tony Hall: Wrong not to
OL,5,Csack Bashir after Diana interview
OL,6, A former BBC director general has said
OL,7, it was the "wrong judgement" in
OL,8, hindsight not to sack Martin Bashir
OL,9, over his behaviour in the run-up to his
OL,10, 1995 interview with Princess Diana.
OL,12,FAt the time, Tony Hall investigated
OL,13,FBashir's faking of bank documents over
OL,14,Fquestions about whether the reporter
OL,15,Fhad used them to secure the scoop.
OL,17,FHe told a committee of MPs: "We trusted
OL,18,Fhim and we clearly shouldn't have."
OL,20,FCommittee chairman Julian Knight said
OL,21,Fthere had been "a failure of morality".
